<L>__{exterior jane, on main street}
<A>__{she has the letter in her hand. she approaches the mailbox, opens the mailbox door, and then glances at the envelope again.}
<L>__{exterior the envelope, jane's pov}
<A>__{addressed in pencil, it says: father lester lowe holy family rectory; 149 main street tarker's mills, maine.}
<L>__{exterior jane, at the mailbox}
<A>__{she drops the letter in with the air of a girl lighting the fuse on a packet of high explosives. she turns away toward home.}
<L>__{interior the rectory living room, with lester lowe}
<A>__{he's standing at the window and looking out. the torn open envelope is on an end table beside him. he's holding the lined sheet of paper in his hand. an expression of bitter hate twists his features, and he slowly crumples the paper in his fist.}
